tpptp Exploration

I explored different values of $t^{\prime\prime}/t^{\prime}$ (denoted as tpptp in the code) to find the optimal value for fitting the magnon dispersion data. The values explored are: [0, -0.2, -0.4, -0.5, -0.6, -0.7].

For each tpptp value: - The fit is performed using the self-consistent-loop method - $U$ is the only free parameter - $\frac{t}{U}$ and $\frac{t^\prime}{t}$ are looped over - The best $\chi^2$ value is recorded
